Build ubuntu-noble sdcard for orangepi 5 plus and rockpi4b:

Input files: ../rootfs-ubuntu-noble/linaro-rootfs.img
                                   /linaro-esp.img

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
sudo mount /dev/sda2 /mnt
sudo cp ./rtlbt/* /mnt/lib/firmware/rtl_bt && sync && sudo umount /mnt
Eject NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD from PC.

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD to orangepi 5 plus/rockpi4b. Plugin ethernet cable to orangepi 5 plus.
(opi5+) Esc -> Boot Manager -> ( sdcard, emmc userdata or the last UEFI )
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
(rockpi4b) Setup wifi.
Disable power saving, auto suspend and screen saver.
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt dist-upgrade
sync
free
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check if Ubuntu is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Check audio driver: ( pulseaudio or pipewire )
pactl info

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools ffmpeg mpv glmark2-es2-wayland pandoc vlc vlc-plugin-video-output vsftpd

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2-wayland

systemctl --user restart pipewire
systemctl --user restart wireplumber
sudo systemctl restart alsa-restore
aplay -l     ( power down / up if no hdmi show up )
pavucontrol  ( select hdmi0 as default )

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa
sudo apt update; sudo apt upgrade -y;
sudo apt install firefox-esr
firefox -> youtube -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

Do follows on PC, then ftp swan.mp4 to rockpi4b/opi5+.
(
git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
(rockpi4b) ~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan.mp4 --postprocessor-args " -c:v libx264 -b:v 2M -c:a copy"
(opi5+)    ~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan.mp4 --postprocessor-args " -c:v libx265 -b:v 2M -c:a copy"
)

mpv --hwdec=auto-copy swan.mp4
ffplay swan.mp4
cvlc --gl=wgl --glconv=any swan.mp4

(opi5+) Plugin ASUS USB-BT500 bluetooth usb dongle to opi5+.
sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
